{
  "title": "The Terminal Strikes Back",
  "slides": [
    {
      "headlines": "What is Github Copilot CLI",
      "bullets": [
        "A full agentic dev environment in your terminal",
        "Specialized built-in agents — Explore for codebase analysis, Task for builds/tests, Code Review for PR reviews, running in parallel when needed ",
        "Background delegation — prefix any prompt with & to offload work to Copilot cloud agent, freeing your terminal while it works ",
        "Remote control — kick off a Copilot cloud session at home, get a QR code, continue on the train",
        "Deeply extensible — custom agents, markdown-based skills, MCP servers, LSP code intelligence, and hooks at every lifecycle point"
      ]
    },
    {
      "headlines": "Two Operating Modes",
      "sections": [
        {
          "header": "Programmatic Mode",
          "bullets": [
            "copilot -p \"list my open PRs\"",
            "Perfect for scripting and automation"
          ]
        },
        {
          "header": "Interactive Mode",
          "bullets": [
            "Full command access in terminal",
            "Commands start with /"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "headlines": "Essential Commands",
      "bullets": [
        "/update - CLI updates (certain installers)",
        "/models - Switch between available models",
        "/env - Show all extensions",
        "! - to run shell commands"
      ]
    },
    {
      "headlines": "Different Modes",
      "sections": [
        {
          "header": "Modes",
          "bullets": [
            "Normal mode - Standard operation, ask as it goes along",
            "Plan mode - Structured planning agent, ask all questions upfront",
            "Autopilot - Autonomous agents"
          ]
        },
        {
          "header": "Asks for rights",
          "bullets": [
            "Asks for trust of folder",
            "Asks for using tools, cli commands, editing files, accessing web pages",
